### Step 1 — Login
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "login": "admin",
  "password": "admin"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("token", response.body.token);
  client.global.set("run", String(Date.now()));
%}

###

### Step 2 — Create brand
POST {{host}}/catalog/brands
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Purchase Flow Brand {{run}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("brandId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 3 — Create supplier party
POST {{host}}/party
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "personType": "LEGAL_ENTITY",
  "cnpj": "12345678000195",
  "legalName": "Fornecedor Purchase {{run}}",
  "name": "Fornecedor {{run}}",
  "customer": false,
  "supplier": true,
  "salesperson": false
}

> {%
  client.global.set("supplierId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 4 — Associate supplier to brand
POST {{host}}/catalog/brands/{{brandId}}/suppliers/{{supplierId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 5 — Create category
POST {{host}}/catalog/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Purchase Flow Category {{run}}",
  "parentId": null
}

> {%
  client.global.set("categoryId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 6 — Create size
POST {{host}}/catalog/sizes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "M-{{run}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("sizeId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 7 — Create product with SKU (triggers PurchaseOpened + PurchaseUpdated)
# ProductSkuCreated event → ProductSkuCreatedListener → CreateOrUpdatePurchaseUseCase
# → Purchase.create() fires PurchaseOpened, Purchase.addLine() fires PurchaseUpdated
# Product must have purchaseDate set for the listener to create a purchase
POST {{host}}/catalog/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Purchase Flow Product {{run}}",
  "price": 199.90,
  "cost": 89.90,
  "purchaseDate": "2026-07-01",
  "colorId": null,
  "brandId": "{{brandId}}",
  "categoryId": "{{categoryId}}",
  "skus": [
    {
      "barcode": "PR-{{run}}",
      "sizeId": "{{sizeId}}",
      "implantationQty": 10
    }
  ]
}

> {%
  client.global.set("productId", response.body.id);
  client.global.set("skuId", response.body.skus[0].id);
%}

###

### Step 8 — Get purchase by supplierId filter
GET {{host}}/purchases?supplierId={{supplierId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

> {%
  client.global.set("purchaseId", response.body.content[0].id);
%}

###

### Step 9 — Add payable (will be removed in next step)
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/payables
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dueDate": "2026-08-01",
  "amount": 50.00
}

> {%
  client.global.set("payableId", response.body.payables[0].id);
%}

###

### Step 10 — Remove payable
DELETE {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/payables/{{payableId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 11 — Add correct payable (amount matches lines total)
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/payables
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dueDate": "2026-08-15",
  "amount": 899.00
}

###

### Step 12 — Update observations
PUT {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/observations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "observations": "Compra revisada {{run}}"
}

###

### Step 13 — Confirm purchase
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 14 — Get confirmed purchase (status must be CONFIRMED)
GET {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 15 — Create second product SKU for new purchase (different purchaseDate → new purchase)
POST {{host}}/catalog/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Purchase Flow Product 2 {{run}}",
  "price": 149.90,
  "cost": 59.90,
  "purchaseDate": "2026-08-01",
  "colorId": null,
  "brandId": "{{brandId}}",
  "categoryId": "{{categoryId}}",
  "skus": [
    {
      "barcode": "PR2-{{run}}",
      "sizeId": "{{sizeId}}",
      "implantationQty": 5
    }
  ]
}

> {%
  client.global.set("productId2", response.body.id);
  client.global.set("skuId2", response.body.skus[0].id);
%}

###

### Step 16 — Get second purchase (status=OPEN, different purchaseDate)
GET {{host}}/purchases?supplierId={{supplierId}}&status=OPEN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

> {%
  client.global.set("purchase2Id", response.body.content[0].id);
%}

###

### Step 17 — Cancel second purchase
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchase2Id}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 18 — List CONFIRMED purchases
GET {{host}}/purchases?status=CONFIRMED
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### --- Error cases ---

### Error 1 — Add payable to CONFIRMED purchase → 422
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/payables
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dueDate": "2026-09-01",
  "amount": 100.00
}

###

### Error 2 — Confirm unknown purchase → 404
POST {{host}}/purchases/9999999999999/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Error 3 — Add payable with missing amount field → 400
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/payables
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dueDate": "2026-09-01"
}

###

### Error 4 — Cancel confirmed purchase → 422
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
